## 2026-06-23 - ACS-GOV-02 Future Integrity Gate

Before any L4 Consolidated assessment, every canonical action in this registry must be re-verified as `BLOCKED` against the same evidence revision being assessed.

Gate failure conditions:

- any action is no longer `BLOCKED`
- a canonical identifier or mapping is missing
- blocked semantics are weakened or made ambiguous
- runtime/source behavior contradicts the registry
- portfolio/global mutation is treated as generally open authority

Explicit writable/governed register tasks may authorize only their bounded documentation writes. General `portfolio.global_registers.mutate` authority remains controlled and re-blocked after completion.
